explanation: This solution uses a sliding window approach to check all substrings of the given string that have the same length as the total length of all words. It uses two hash maps to store the frequency of each word in the words array and in the current substring. If the frequency of a word in the substring exceeds the frequency in the words array, the substring is not a concatenated string. The solution returns a list of starting indices of all concatenated substrings.

